        <num>CCRP 594</num>
        <heading>594.  Method of trial; time for disposition</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 594.  Method of trial; time for disposition
Double jeopardy may be raised at any time, but only once, and shall be tried by the court alone.  If raised during the trial, a hearing thereon may be deferred until the end of the trial.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112637</p>
